  "title": "Managing acid soils for reclaiming livelihoods in Ethiopia",
  "abstract": "Soil acidification is the result of a complex set of processes caused both naturally and by human activity. It limits plant growth because of conditions that increase base element deficiencies, Phosphorus-fixation and toxicities of Aluminum, Manganese and Hydrogen ions.",
